<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/high.css">
    <title>regions</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header class="header">
        <h1>High level</h1>
    </header>

    <main class="main-content">
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Rajasthan, Gujarat, Andra Pradesh, Karnataka, Telangana are the states face acute water shortages due to low rainfall,over-extraction of groundwater,and high demand</h2>
                <h3>Tips and technologies implemented in many states</h3>
                <div class="card">
                    <h2>1. Efficient Water Use in Agriculture</h2>
                    <p>Drip Irrigation: Delivers water directly to the plant roots, reducing wastage. Widely adopted in arid regions.</p>
                    <p>Mulching: Retains soil moisture and reduces evaporation.</p>
                    <p>Drought-Resistant Crops: Planting crops that require less water.</p>
                    <p>Rainwater Harvesting in Fields: Captures and stores rainwater for irrigation.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://www.prinsco.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/PrinscoAgEfficiencyInfographic.jpg" alt="Efficient Water Use in Agriculture">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>2. Rainwater Harvesting in Urban Areas</h2>
                    <p>Mandate rooftop rainwater harvesting to recharge groundwater.</p>
                    <p>Community Ponds and Tanks: Create or revive traditional water bodies for rainwater storage.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                    <img src="https://www.frontiersin.org/files/Articles/1025665/fenvs-11-1025665-HTML/image_m/fenvs-11-1025665-g008.jpg" alt="Rainwater Harvesting in Urban Areas"></div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>3. Wastewater Treatment and Reuse</h2>
                    <p>Greywater Recycling: Treat wastewater from households (e.g., showers and sinks) for non-potable uses like irrigation and flushing.</p>
                    <p>Industrial Water Reuse: Enforce water recycling in industries.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://vertassets.blob.core.windows.net/image/f7d2b22c/f7d2b22c-642e-4ed6-b9ff-729e20419946/water_reuse_cycle.jpg" alt="Wastewater Treatment and Reuse">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>4. Groundwater Recharge</h2>
                    <p>Artificial Recharge Structures: Use check dams, percolation tanks, or recharge wells to increase groundwater levels.</p>
                    <p>Afforestation: Plant trees to improve water infiltration into the ground.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/08/2f/3e/082f3e983aa9c4f58e6fec652e7c0781.jpg" alt="Groundwater Recharge">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="card">
                    <h2>5. Urban Water Management</h2>
                    <p>Water-Saving Fixtures: Promote low-flow taps, dual-flush toilets, and aerated showerheads.</p>
                    <p>Leakage Management: Regularly inspect and repair water supply networks to prevent loss.</p>
                    <div class="image-container">
                      <img src="https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20220831135941/WaterCollection-768x384.jpg" alt="Urban Water Management">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                
            </div>

        </div>
    </main>

</body>
</html>
